1) version information => VERSION

2) compile
make

3) clean
make clean

4) vector length for double prec. array (SIMD width/64) 4th line of qws.h
5) vector length for single prec. array (SIMD width/32) 5th line of qws.h
6) it could be better to repalce functions of  qwsintrin.h by SIMD instructions

7) 4D local lattice size, (lx ...), proc. num (px ...) tolerance of outer and inner DD solver 
are arguments of test program. When tol<0, iter will be maxiter and solution may become NaN
#      lx ly lz lt px py pz pt tolerance(outer) tolerance(inner)
./main 16  4  4  4  1  1  1  1            1e-14            1e-6

8) test cases
             ./main  4 1 1 1   1 1 1 1    -1   -1 > CASE_4111_1111    # with vlend=vlens=2
             ./main  4 1 1 1   1 1 1 1    -1   -1 > CASE_4111_1111_HP # with vlend=vlens=2, half_prec
mpirun -n 1  ./main 32 6 4 3   1 1 1 1    -1   -1 > CASE0
mpirun -n 2  ./main 32 6 4 3   1 1 1 2    -1   -1 > CASE1
mpirun -n 2  ./main 32 3 4 4   1 1 1 2    -1   -1 > CASE2
mpirun -n 2  ./main 32 3 6 4   1 1 1 2    -1   -1 > CASE3
mpirun -n 2  ./main 32 6 6 2   1 1 1 2    -1   -1 > CASE4
mpirun -n 2  ./main 32 6 6 4   1 1 1 2    -1   -1 > CASE5
mpirun -n 2  ./main 32 6 6 8   1 1 1 2    -1   -1 > CASE6
mpirun -n 8  ./main 32 6 4 3   1 2 2 2    -1   -1 > CASE7
mpirun -n 16 ./main 32 6 4 3   4 4 1 1    -1   -1 > CASE8
mpirun -n 16 ./main 32 6 4 3   1 1 4 4    -1   -1 > CASE9
